    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-06-21T23:40:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-06-21T23:40:00-05:00" n="46"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d46">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">756.94/147: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Singapore</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Patton</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Singapore</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-22T12:00:00+07:20"
                            >June 22, 1940—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received June 22—4:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Conferences now being held in Singapore by military, naval, and government
                    officials in view of the critical situation which may result from Japan making
                    further efforts to develop her new order in Asia. One of the chief subjects
                    under discussion is the disposition of oil fields and refineries at Miri and
                    Sandakan as well as in Netherlands Indies which it is not feasible at the
                    present time to protect. It is understood that preparations have been made to
                    destroy all refineries in the event that the Japanese attempt to occupy them.
                    Naval authorities believed that Japan will attempt some such action if the
                    United States curtails oil supplies to Japan.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Patton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
